        <etym xml:lang="ru">По значению близко к %ifaxs%i ‘бок’ и, вероятно, одного корня с ним.
                Исходная индоиранская основа %i*pag-%i; отсюда, с одной стороны, %i*pag-s-%i →
                %ipakša-%i → %ifaxs%i; с другой — %i*pāg-%i → %ipāj-%i → %ipāz-%i → %ifaz%i. В
                иранских языках находим в значении некоторых частей тела (‘грудь’, ‘лицо’) и в
                значении ‘поверхность’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                                        ><lang/><w>poz</w><gloss><q>грудь</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>pūz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sgy"><lang/><w>puz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
                                ><lang/><w>fuz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="khw"
                                ><lang/><w>pāz</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из
                                иран.)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                                Iranian)</note><gloss><q>грудь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="zza"><lang/><w>ρīzε</w><gloss><q>живот</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><lang/><w>*pāz-(pʼz-)</w><gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned>,<note
                        n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                        ><lang/><w>p'zуу</w><gloss><q>частица</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                                ><lang/><w>pāysa-(-pāza)</w><gloss><q>лицо</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                        ><lang/><w>pājas-</w><gloss><q>лик</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>поверхность</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w>pājasya-</w><gloss><q>брюхо (у
                        животных)</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Сюда же, вероятно, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"
                        ><lang/><w>Fach</w><gloss><q>часть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>отдел</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>zwei-fach</w></mentioned> = ос. %idy-vaz-yg%i). Ср.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_faxs"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                        536</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                                /><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOAS"
                                /><biblScope>1948 XII 323–326; 1949 XIII
                136</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">In the meaning it is close to %ifaxs%i ‘side’ and, probably, they are of
                the same root. The initial Indo-Iranian stem is %i*pag-%i; on the one hand, there is
                %i*pag-s-%i → %ipakša-%i → %ifaxs%i; on the other hand, there is %i*pāg-%i →
                %ipāj-%i → %ipāz-%i → %ifaz%i. In Iranian languages, this word is found in the
                meaning of some parts of a body (‘chest’, ‘face’) and in the meaning ‘surface’. Cf.
                        <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
                        ><lang/><w>poz</w><gloss><q>chest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="wbl"><lang/><w>pūz-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
                                ><lang/><w>puz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"
                                ><lang/><w>fuz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="khw"
                                ><lang/><w>pāz</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из
                                иран.)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                                Iranian)</note><gloss><q>chest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="zza"><lang/><w>ρīzε</w><gloss><q>stomach</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                                ><lang/><w>*pāz-(pʼz-)</w><gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned>,<note
                        n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note>
                <mentioned xml:lang="sog"
                        ><lang/><w>p'zуу</w><gloss><q>particle</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>81</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                                ><lang/><w>pāysa-(-pāza)</w><gloss><q>face</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pājas-</w><gloss><q>representation of
                                        face</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                                        ><w/><gloss><q>surface</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w>pājasya-</w><gloss><q>belly (of an
                        animal)</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The word <mentioned xml:lang="de"
                                ><lang/><w>Fach</w><gloss><q>part</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="de"><w/><gloss><q>division</q></gloss></mentioned>, is probably
                related to it as well (<mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/><w>zwei-fach</w></mentioned>
                = Ossetic %idy-vaz-yg%i). Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_faxs"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                        536</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Bailey._Asica"
                                /><biblScope>11</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOAS"
                                /><biblScope>1948 XII 323–326; 1949 XIII
                136</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
